inciple of proportionality. The use of length of sentence is one way of seeking to do this; another way is to leave it to the judge’s discretion in the circumstances of the particular case as part of sentencing..</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="15" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Do you think it would be feasible to link the right to vote to rehabilitation?  For example, providing prisoners with an opportunity to be educated in the democratic system of the UK and then allowing them to apply to be enfranchised? </span></li><ol type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 67.33pt; padding-left:4.67pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Do you think this might help pri</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">soners reintegrate into society?</span></li></ol></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">That would be complex and expensive</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="16" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">There has been some suggestion of allowing disenfranchised prisoners the option of applying to be re-enfranchised.  How might this work in the judicial system?</span